subSubSection.paragraph:
Abdomen (
Fig. 15
) blackish brown except syntergosternite and epandrium brown, with grayish white pruinescence; tergites 2–6 with 1 row setae on posterior margin. Male genitalia (
Figs. 16–20
): syntergosternite slender, incomplete circular in anterior view, breakage connected by membrane. Epandrium slender. Surstylus broad with seta, tapering apically. Hypandrium H-shaped with a pair of distinct inner process. Gonopod tubiform, wider than aedeagus in lateral view, with 3 long hairs. Aedeagus slender basally, with a pair of dorsal sclerites, without apical concave. Aedeagal apodeme tubiform, shorter than 1/2 length of aedeagus.
